      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TYTATE NZ (5) is a newcomer to the Chantal Turpin yard from NZ where she was last seen scoring by 1.6 metres in the Breeders Stakes at Alexandra Park. Readied with a trial and can make an immediate impact. LUX AETERNA (7) has been racing well of late. Came from the back row for a 3.4m fourth when tackling some good mares at her latest appearance. Won the previous time she raced here. The driver has some work to do from this wide starting position but with even luck she has the quality to take this out. BELLA DANZA (1) will be fitter for recent racing and gets her best draw of the campaign so far so look for improvement. SHEZ SWEET LOUISE NZ (4) scored a win at this circuit and distance last time and has a good third-up record so can perform well again.",
